&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;The Operations team manages our worldwide distribution network and is responsible for authenticating our sneakers, fulfilling orders and ensuring on-time delivery to buyers. Through our technological innovation and logistical efficiency, you will join a team that prides itself on being the most trusted marketplace in the industry while shipping and processing tens of millions of products for our global buyers and sellers.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Overview&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;As the Operations Supervisor at GOAT, you will be responsible for the day-to-day leadership and management of GOAT’s local facility. The ideal candidate for this role is highly organized, detail-oriented, analytical, and thrives in a fast-paced, ever-evolving dynamic start up environment.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;Strong decision-making skills will be critical for this role as the operational needs of the facility can fluctuate day-to-day. The planning, organization, and execution of completing operational goals can be challenging during our current growth, so it will be important that this position will work as a calm, objective focused leader to make sure targets are met daily.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In this role, you will:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;Promoting a strong safety culture and healthy work environment&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;Lead, manage and cross-train a team associates and service providers&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;Ensure best implementation in operations of inbound, inventory, verification, outbound, return, fulfillment and logistics&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;Work with multiple departments to resolve potential delays and slippages&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;Spearhead continuous improvements to increase efficiency, quality and reduce costs&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;Engage in cost-benefit analyses, seeking to obtain best prices for materials and overseeing production methods to optimize output to peak efficiency levels&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;Regularly monitor expenses, diminishing spend where possible if necessary to stay on budget&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;Collect data and analyze trends and behaviors that will allow the organization to improve handling flow and customer experience&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;Set the tone of the leadership team with a calm, positive, focused and forward motion leadership style in a high pressure, fast work environment with consistent changes&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;Be knowledgeable of the company’s goals&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;Other duties

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At GOAT Group, the Business Development team drives supply growth across our marketplace. We&#39;re looking for a product-focused, data-driven associate to support supply initiatives across all sourcing channels. This role combines uncovering insights in the data and leveraging AI and other tools to build processes and drive action.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In this role, you will:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use SQL extensively to analyze marketplace performance data and uncover actionable insights across key metrics (liquidity, active quantity, pricing, engagement, and sell-through) surfacing trends, opportunities, and risks to stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze sales, stock on-hand, and on-order at the style/color/size level to make recommendations on style selections, unit allocations, and pricing strategies that balance revenue opportunity with profitability&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform exploratory / “ad-hoc” data analysis to support various global strategic initiatives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay on top of product trends across categories and conduct competitive intelligence research to identify emerging areas and maintain a best-in-class assortment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor active supply metrics to ensure marketplace supply meets future demand and track initiatives like SKU-based incentives to measure opportunity recapture&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain SQL-based dashboards that support the Business Development team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evaluate current reporting and seek out new ways to enhance how performance is tracked&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support projects and tasks from manager and other key stakeholders on an as-needed basis&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and optimize workflows using templates and AI tools across systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are looking for:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2-4 years of experience in an analytical role (planning, buying, supply chain, e-commerce, or similar - fashion + footwear a plus)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong SQL skills with the ability to independently query large datasets and turn findings into actionable next steps&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comprehension of retail math and e-commerce metrics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Genuine passion for product and trends across categories&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficient in SQL and Excel&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfort using AI tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to move quickly from data to decisions and manage multiple projects independently&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent attention to detail and ownership mindset&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Research skills: gathering and organizing data to provide actionable recommendations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Scrappy, resourceful mindset with strong work ethic&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bonus:&lt;/strong&gt; Experience with BI tools (Looker, Tableau), Python, or inventory planning&lt;/p&gt;
